Unknown characters (a man, a woman, the nurse...)
key="gen-man(woman)-01(02,03,04...) - generic man (anonymous) ALTERNATIVA: no key/who
Example: <person key="gen-man-01"> - <said who="gen-man-01"...>


Ex.
                    <person key="BudKorpenning">
                        <persName>
                            <forename>Bud</forename> 
                            <surname>Korpenning</surname>
                        </persName>
                    </person> 

Secondo nome: @sort
                    <person key="EdThatcher">
                        <persName>
                            <forename>Edward</forename>
                            <forename full="abb" sort="2">C.</forename>
                            <surname>Thatcher</surname>
                        </persName>
                    </person> 

Surname: birth/married
                    <person key="EllenThatcher">
                        <persName>
                            <addName type="nickname">Elaine</addName>
                            <surname type="birth">Thatcher</surname>
                            <surname type="married">Oglethorpe</surname>
                        </persName>
                    </person>

Nickname:
                    <person key="EllenThatcher">
                        <persName>
                            <addName type="nickname">Ellie</addName>
                        </persName>
                    </person>

Forename Jimmy vs. James: birth
                    <person key="JimmyHerf">
                        <persName>
                            <addName type="birth">James</addName>
                        </persName>
                    </person>
                
Honorifics:
                    <person key="EllenThatcher">
                        <persName>
                            <roleName type="honorific" full="abb">Mrs.</roleName> 
                            <surname type="birth">Thatcher</surname> 
                        </persName>
                    </person>

foreign:
<foreign xml:lang="fr">#</foreign>  

Honorific + foreign:
                    <person key="EmileRigaud">
                        <persName>
                            <roleName type="honorific" full="abb"><foreign xml:lang="fr">Mme.</foreign></roleName> 
                            <surname>Rigaud</surname>
                        </persName>
                    </person>

                    <person key="EmileLoustec">
                        <persName>
                            <roleName type="honorific"><foreign xml:lang="fr">Monsieur</foreign></roleName> 
                            <surname>Loustec</surname> 
                        </persName>
                    </person>             

Dialoghi:                    
<said who="#" aloud="true" direct="true">

Thought:
                    <said who="#EdThatcher" aloud="false" direct="false">Well poor little 
                    <person key="SusieThatcher">
                        <persName>
                            <forename>Susie</forename> 
                        </persName>
                    </person>                    
                    wouldn't like me to be here. . . . Everything for her and the bonny wee bairn.</said>

